In the given autonomous race car stack, the inputs available to us are the LiDAR scan (topic /scan) and the raw odometry (topic /odom) data published by the Gazebo simulation. RoboRacerEnv acts as the bridge between the student Jupyter notebook and the Gazebo simulation. It converts /scan and /odom into an observation vector for the RL model, and converts the selected RL action into a /cmd_vel command for the car.
This assignment gives you an understanding of how the important components of an RL package are constructed such as, 
•	Observation vectors from /scan and /odom. 
•	Value functions in RL (DQN and PPO)
•	Reward Functions
using the agent : car, environment : gazebo simulation
From the given picture the whole RL loop is defined. And by referring to the current implementation of roboracer_rl package, complete the tasks below.

--------------------------------
RL loop:

Gazebo simulation
    publishes
/scan + /odom
    read by
RoboRacerEnv
    converted into observation vector
    given to
student Jupyter notebook / train_student.py
    DQN/PPO selects action
    sent back through
RoboRacerEnv
    publishes
/cmd_vel
    controls
Gazebo car

