Task 1 : The Observation Vector
Reference file in the RL stack: gym_env.py --> _observation(), _sectorize_scan()

The agent cannot directly see the Gazebo world or the track. It only receives a numerical observation vector built from the LiDAR scan topic /scan and odometry topic /odom. In this task, you will understand how RoboRacerEnv converts raw sensor data into sectorized LiDAR values, speed information, and previous steering information used as input to the RL model.

--------------------------------

Task 2 : The Reward Function
Reference file: gym_env.py --> _reward()

The agent learns from a single scalar reward given after every action. This reward defines what "good driving" means for the RoboRacer car. In this task, you will test and reason about reward terms such as forward movement, wall distance, steering smoothness, and crash penalty, and understand how they shape the learned driving behavior.

---------------------------------

Task 3 : The Value Function and Training with DQN
Reference file: train.py --> DQN configuration block
Reference file: train_student.py --> student training script

This part of the RL loop turns an observation into an action using a neural network. In DQN, the network estimates the action-value function Q(s, a), which tells how good each possible action is in the current state. In this task, you will understand the DQN training script, examine important hyperparameters, and see how RoboRacerEnv connects Gazebo sensor topics /scan and /odom to the RL model and publishes the selected action back to /cmd_vel.

